    "We calculate ∥Em * (u n)∥ P d = sup    Em * (u n)(f, π 1,..., π d): ∥f ∥ L d j=1 Lip(π j) ≤ 1    = sup    Q u n f det Dπ dL d: ∥f ∥ L d j=1 Lip(π j) ≤ 1   .Therefore, we see that if a constant C satisfying (3.5) exists, then the sequence u n does not satisfy (ii) of Definition 1.3.",
    "On the other hand, if a sequence u n can be found such that both (i) and (ii) of Definition 1.3 hold, no such constant C can exist.For the final statement, we observe that if Conjecture 1.1 holds, then Em * is surjective and therefore has closed range.",
    "A Hahn-Banach separation theoremThe point of this section is to develop a tool from functional analysis, which will allow us to pass from a particularly strong result on the operator Em (into L ∞) to a result for the operator Em * (on L 1 (Q)), asserting eventually strong Lipschitz non-regularity for the prescribed Jacobian equation.We use the following notation.",
